79. intactis ‘ clean white.’ Tarpeias arces. On the th first of January the consuls elect entered 011 their office and went in solemn processioa to the Capitol. The Capitoline hill has two summits, the Capitol, on which the great temple of Jupiter stood, and the Arx. The Tarpeian roek, from which criminals ; were thrown, was part of the Capitol. The names Capitolium, Arx, and Mons Tarpeius are however often used loosely by the poets to denote the whole hill.
